1
00:02:41,005 --> 00:02:43,445
Hello, admitting.

2
00:02:43,485 --> 00:02:46,725
This is Saperstein.
Where is he?

3
00:02:48,725 --> 00:02:50,325
He's cleared admitting?

4
00:02:50,405 --> 00:02:53,565
Right. Bring him in.

5
00:03:02,885 --> 00:03:04,485
He's coming.

6
00:03:04,565 --> 00:03:06,165
Good, good.

7
00:03:15,005 --> 00:03:16,125
Trent?

8
00:03:16,205 --> 00:03:17,765
John J.

9
00:03:17,845 --> 00:03:19,925
Put him in number nine.

10
00:03:24,365 --> 00:03:25,685
You son of a bitch!

11
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:30,605
Hang on to him.

12
00:03:40,485 --> 00:03:41,725
Get him in there!

13
00:03:41,805 --> 00:03:43,845
No, not me!

14
00:03:43,925 --> 00:03:45,725
No, wait, wait!

15
00:03:45,805 --> 00:03:47,045
This is wrong.

16
00:03:47,125 --> 00:03:50,125
Look, I'm sorry about the balls!

17
00:03:50,205 --> 00:03:52,565
It was a lucky shot, that's all!

18
00:03:52,605 --> 00:03:54,405
Wait!

19
00:04:07,005 --> 00:04:08,805
I'm not insane.

20
00:04:08,885 --> 00:04:10,005
You hear me?

21
00:04:10,045 --> 00:04:12,205
I'm not insane!

22
00:04:12,285 --> 00:04:14,445
I'm not if he's not!

23
00:04:16,245 --> 00:04:18,845
Me neither!

24
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:24,245
I'm not insane!

25
00:05:05,925 --> 00:05:10,485
We've only just begun

26
00:05:10,565 --> 00:05:13,525
Not the Carpenters, too.

27
00:05:16,805 --> 00:05:20,125
So let me go

28
00:05:59,965 --> 00:06:03,685
This is a rotten way to end it.

29
00:06:03,765 --> 00:06:05,125
This is not the ending.

30
00:06:05,205 --> 00:06:06,565
You haven't read it yet.

31
00:06:34,365 --> 00:06:35,525
All right.

32
00:06:35,605 --> 00:06:36,885
Came in this afternoon?

33
00:06:36,965 --> 00:06:39,725
Yes. How did you
get here so fast?

34
00:06:39,805 --> 00:06:41,285
We've been monitoring
all admissions...

35
00:06:41,365 --> 00:06:42,645
through police
and paramedic channels.

36
00:06:42,685 --> 00:06:43,765
This one fit the symptoms.

37
00:06:43,805 --> 00:06:47,445
Do you think he's one of them?

38
00:06:47,525 --> 00:06:48,965
Mr. Saperstein, I promise you...

39
00:06:49,045 --> 00:06:50,645
that's what I'm here
to find out.

40
00:06:50,685 --> 00:06:53,085
Things must be getting
pretty bad out there...

41
00:06:53,165 --> 00:06:54,765
to bring youfellas in.

42
00:06:55,765 --> 00:06:56,885
Is this it?

43
00:06:59,085 --> 00:07:00,565
Did he make any requests?

44
00:07:00,645 --> 00:07:02,725
Just...

45
00:07:02,805 --> 00:07:04,045
one.

46
00:07:04,125 --> 00:07:05,165
A, uh...

47
00:07:05,245 --> 00:07:08,045
single black crayon.

48
00:07:29,485 --> 00:07:31,285
Hang on.

49
00:07:36,845 --> 00:07:37,925
What's up?

50
00:07:38,005 --> 00:07:40,925
My name is Dr. Wrenn...

51
00:07:41,005 --> 00:07:42,885
and I am going to try
and get you out of here.

52
00:07:45,005 --> 00:07:47,605
After all my redecorating?

53
00:07:47,645 --> 00:07:49,845
No. I think I'll stay.

54
00:07:49,925 --> 00:07:52,445
There's a guard with a pair
of swollen testicles...

55
00:07:52,525 --> 00:07:54,645
who swears you wanted
out of here.

56
00:07:55,885 --> 00:07:58,245
I, uh, well...

57
00:07:58,325 --> 00:08:00,405
I've changed my mind.

58
00:08:00,485 --> 00:08:02,685
I see.

59
00:08:02,765 --> 00:08:05,725
The crosses are a nice touch.

60
00:08:05,805 --> 00:08:08,685
They'd almost have
to keep you in here...

61
00:08:08,765 --> 00:08:12,245
once they'd seen these,
wouldn't they, John?

62
00:08:12,285 --> 00:08:13,805
Got a smoke?

63
00:08:27,885 --> 00:08:30,205
You're waiting to hear
about my "them," aren't you?

64
00:08:30,245 --> 00:08:31,525
Your what?

65
00:08:32,965 --> 00:08:34,605
My "them."

66
00:08:35,685 --> 00:08:37,685
Every paranoid schizophrenic
has one...

67
00:08:37,725 --> 00:08:40,605
a "them," a "they," an "it."

68
00:08:40,685 --> 00:08:44,245
And you want to hear
about my "them," don't you?

69
00:08:44,285 --> 00:08:46,205
I want to know how you got here.

70
00:08:49,845 --> 00:08:53,245
Things are turning to shit
out there, aren't they?

71
00:08:54,925 --> 00:08:56,925
Let's talk about you.

72
00:08:59,605 --> 00:09:01,245
Your dime.

73
00:09:03,005 --> 00:09:05,005
I'm, uh...

74
00:09:05,085 --> 00:09:09,365
I was an insurance investigator,
freelance.

75
00:09:10,885 --> 00:09:12,805
Checked outfunny claims,
frauds...

76
00:09:12,885 --> 00:09:14,765
the usual kind of thing.

77
00:09:14,845 --> 00:09:18,725
And lately I'd been working
for a firm here in the city.

78
00:09:18,805 --> 00:09:25,365
And all of this started
with the disappearance.

79
00:09:26,965 --> 00:09:28,525
The Sutter Cane...

80
00:09:28,605 --> 00:09:30,045
disappearance.

81
00:09:36,125 --> 00:09:38,605
It's a little hot in here,
isn't it?

82
00:09:38,685 --> 00:09:39,925
It's boiling.

83
00:09:41,565 --> 00:09:43,245
How long I gotta be here?

84
00:09:43,325 --> 00:09:45,205
I mean, uh...

85
00:09:45,245 --> 00:09:47,445
I took care
of all that paperwork.

86
00:09:47,485 --> 00:09:49,405
The check was supposed
to be here three weeks ago.

87
00:09:49,485 --> 00:09:51,925
Right? Isn't that right?

88
00:09:52,005 --> 00:09:53,885
Well, usually, yeah,
that's the way it goes...

89
00:09:53,965 --> 00:09:57,365
but I just have a few final
questions about the fire.

90
00:09:57,445 --> 00:09:58,485
More questions.

91
00:09:58,565 --> 00:10:00,045
I've answered
all your questions.

92
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:01,165
Enough's enough.

93
00:10:01,245 --> 00:10:03,885
It was supposed
to be cut and dried.

94
00:10:03,965 --> 00:10:05,725
We'll be out of here
in a minute.

95
00:10:05,805 --> 00:10:08,245
See, Robby here,
he owns the company.

96
00:10:08,325 --> 00:10:11,285
And he's hired me to see that
things go smoothly, understand?

97
00:10:11,325 --> 00:10:14,045
It's just a little thing,
but, see...

98
00:10:14,125 --> 00:10:16,005
Robby takes the view
that it was you...

99
00:10:16,085 --> 00:10:19,085
who burned down your own
warehouse on Northern Boulevard.

100
00:10:19,165 --> 00:10:20,885
Me? That's horseshit.

101
00:10:20,965 --> 00:10:22,325
That was all my own stuff
in that warehouse.

102
00:10:22,365 --> 00:10:23,445
That's my whole life.

103
00:10:23,485 --> 00:10:26,205
Believe me, I sympathize.

104
00:10:26,285 --> 00:10:27,925
You're really starting to sweat.

105
00:10:27,965 --> 00:10:30,005
Shall I turn on
the air conditioning?

106
00:10:30,045 --> 00:10:31,445
Oh, no, I'm fine.

107
00:10:31,485 --> 00:10:32,885
- You sure?
- Yeah.

108
00:10:34,125 --> 00:10:36,085
I'm running a little late.

109
00:10:36,165 --> 00:10:38,205
Supposed to pick up my wife.

110
00:10:38,285 --> 00:10:40,405
Oh, yeah, your wife.

111
00:10:40,445 --> 00:10:42,165
She's a great lady.

112
00:10:43,325 --> 00:10:45,045
You know her?

113
00:10:45,125 --> 00:10:46,925
No, not really.
We just met briefly.

114
00:10:47,005 --> 00:10:50,965
You know, when I went round
to check up on your story.

115
00:10:51,005 --> 00:10:52,205
We have these photographs...

116
00:10:52,285 --> 00:10:56,045
of your wife
tooling around town...

117
00:10:56,125 --> 00:10:57,325
wearing various articles...

118
00:10:57,405 --> 00:11:00,165
that you claim
were destroyed in the fire.

119
00:11:00,245 --> 00:11:03,245
No, that's impossible.

120
00:11:05,645 --> 00:11:08,925
No, this is all stuff
I boughtfor her myseif.

121
00:11:09,005 --> 00:11:10,565
See, the problem is...

122
00:11:10,645 --> 00:11:12,925
when I went round
to talk to her...

123
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:16,085
it turned out she knew much more
than she thought she did.

124
00:11:16,165 --> 00:11:17,685
Especially...

125
00:11:17,725 --> 00:11:22,765
Especially after I showed her
pictures of Miss Palminteri...

126
00:11:22,845 --> 00:11:24,285
who appears to be wearing...

127
00:11:24,365 --> 00:11:26,125
even more
of your destroyed articles.

128
00:11:28,205 --> 00:11:30,125
Miss Palminteri?

129
00:11:31,485 --> 00:11:33,925
Miss Rosa Palminteri.

130
00:11:35,085 --> 00:11:36,965
A word of advice.

131
00:11:37,045 --> 00:11:41,925
You want to pull a scam,
don't make your wife a partner.

132
00:11:42,005 --> 00:11:43,925
If you do...

133
00:11:44,005 --> 00:11:46,885
don'tfuck around
behind her back.

134
00:11:49,005 --> 00:11:50,885
Trent, beautiful.

135
00:11:50,965 --> 00:11:54,845
Everybody says you got the best
nose for a con in the business.

136
00:11:54,925 --> 00:11:57,845
But to see itfirsthand, I mean,
to watch you work...

137
00:11:57,925 --> 00:11:59,165
is incredible.

138
00:11:59,245 --> 00:12:00,445
Well, it wasn't hard, Robby.

139
00:12:00,525 --> 00:12:03,125
The guy's wife liked me.

140
00:12:03,165 --> 00:12:04,845
Besides, he was an amateur.

141
00:12:04,925 --> 00:12:06,245
It's too easy with amateurs.

142
00:12:06,325 --> 00:12:09,365
You try to figure out who's
professional and who isn't.

143
00:12:09,405 --> 00:12:13,165
That's when it gets fun,
when you run into a pro.

144
00:12:13,245 --> 00:12:15,685
You know, most of my salesmen...

145
00:12:15,765 --> 00:12:17,645
couldn't sniff out
a phony claim...

146
00:12:17,725 --> 00:12:20,045
if their noses
were nailed to it, but you...

147
00:12:20,125 --> 00:12:21,965
man, you never miss.

148
00:12:22,045 --> 00:12:23,125
What's to miss?

149
00:12:23,205 --> 00:12:25,565
You learn to expect the worst
in people, and you get it.

150
00:12:25,645 --> 00:12:28,485
Everyone's looking
to play an angle.

151
00:12:28,565 --> 00:12:31,045
I'm always there
to clean up the mess.

152
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:32,285
I'll tell you what.

153
00:12:32,365 --> 00:12:35,125
You stop freelancing,
join my staff.

154
00:12:35,165 --> 00:12:36,925
I'll make it worth your while.

155
00:12:37,005 --> 00:12:38,925
Forget it, Robby.

156
00:12:39,005 --> 00:12:41,325
I'm my own man.
Nobody pulls my strings.

157
00:12:41,405 --> 00:12:42,645
I'm independent, I'm happy.

158
00:12:42,685 --> 00:12:45,125
Well, be my man one more time.

159
00:12:45,205 --> 00:12:47,885
I'm having quite
a difficult mess with Arcane.

160
00:12:47,965 --> 00:12:49,045
The publishing house?

161
00:12:49,085 --> 00:12:50,805
Yeah, my biggest account.

162
00:12:50,845 --> 00:12:54,845
They justfiled a claim
that cost me millions.

163
00:12:54,925 --> 00:12:56,765
I want you on this right away.

164
00:12:56,805 --> 00:12:57,845
What's the claim?

165
00:12:57,885 --> 00:12:59,325
Sutter Cane is missing.

166
00:12:59,365 --> 00:13:00,565
Who?

167
00:13:00,605 --> 00:13:01,805
Sutter Cane.

168
00:13:21,085 --> 00:13:23,125
Do you read Sutter Cane?

169
00:13:23,205 --> 00:13:24,525
What?

170
00:13:45,085 --> 00:13:47,125
Horror writer Sutter Cane...

171
00:13:47,205 --> 00:13:50,045
a harmless pop phenomenon...

172
00:13:50,085 --> 00:13:52,885
or a deadly mad prophet
of the printed page?

173
00:13:52,925 --> 00:13:56,365
This was the scene today
outside several city bookstores.

174
00:13:56,445 --> 00:13:57,685
Police believe
the riots began...

175
00:13:57,725 --> 00:14:00,125
because the stores
could not meet the demand...

176
00:14:00,165 --> 00:14:03,525
for advance orders
of Sutter Cane's latest novel...

177
00:14:03,605 --> 00:14:05,285
'In the Mouth of Madness."

178
00:14:05,365 --> 00:14:07,765
When does fiction
become religion?

179
00:14:07,845 --> 00:14:09,525
And are his fans dangerous?

180
00:14:09,565 --> 00:14:11,605
Only if you count axes.

181
00:14:11,685 --> 00:14:15,045
In related news, there were
eighteen other stores...

182
00:14:29,085 --> 00:14:30,845
Mr. Harglow will see you now.

183
00:14:30,925 --> 00:14:32,005
Thank you.

184
00:14:33,805 --> 00:14:35,805
You're not listening to me.
I needed it yesterday.

185
00:14:35,885 --> 00:14:37,885
If you wait any longer, it'll be
all over the front page.

186
00:14:37,965 --> 00:14:39,005
Get it done!

187
00:14:39,085 --> 00:14:42,965
Jackson Harglow, Mr. Trent.
I'm pleased to meet you.

188
00:14:43,005 --> 00:14:44,205
It's a pleasure.

189
00:14:44,285 --> 00:14:45,325
Excuse the commotion.

190
00:14:45,405 --> 00:14:48,605
We have something
of a crisis going on.

191
00:14:48,685 --> 00:14:50,205
Everybody out now, please.

192
00:14:50,285 --> 00:14:52,045
I need time with Mr. Trent.

193
00:14:52,125 --> 00:14:54,325
Have Sylvia hold the calls,
and you get Linda in here.

194
00:14:54,365 --> 00:14:57,925
That was great.
I almost left myseif.

195
00:14:58,005 --> 00:14:59,605
Sit down, please.

196
00:14:59,685 --> 00:15:02,645
I am a little short
on patience these days.

197
00:15:02,725 --> 00:15:07,125
So, Mr. Trent,
are youfamiliar with Arcane?

198
00:15:07,205 --> 00:15:08,325
Well, aside from the fact...

199
00:15:08,405 --> 00:15:10,365
that you're insured
by the company I work for...

200
00:15:10,445 --> 00:15:11,925
I never heard of Arcane.
I'm sorry.

201
00:15:12,005 --> 00:15:13,405
You read books?

202
00:15:17,445 --> 00:15:20,365
Linda Styles, John Trent.

203
00:15:20,445 --> 00:15:23,485
Linda reads books for a living.
She's one of our best editors.

204
00:15:23,565 --> 00:15:24,605
Since she joined the firm...

205
00:15:24,685 --> 00:15:27,325
she's been handling
Sutter Cane exclusively.

206
00:15:27,405 --> 00:15:30,845
Isn't he the guy
that writes that horror crap?

207
00:15:30,925 --> 00:15:32,645
Maybe he's too sophisticated
for you.

208
00:15:32,725 --> 00:15:34,045
Sutter Cane happens to be...

209
00:15:34,125 --> 00:15:36,245
this century's
most widely read author.

210
00:15:36,285 --> 00:15:38,165
You can forget
about Stephen King.

211
00:15:38,205 --> 00:15:39,925
Cane outsells them all.

212
00:15:40,005 --> 00:15:43,005
So what happened
to this cash cow of yours?

213
00:15:43,085 --> 00:15:45,805
Cane disappeared two months ago
without a trace.

214
00:15:45,885 --> 00:15:49,245
The police
have turned up nothing.

215
00:15:49,325 --> 00:15:51,925
Who was the last person
to hearfrom him?

216
00:15:51,965 --> 00:15:53,045
His agent.

217
00:15:53,085 --> 00:15:54,645
Cane mailed him
several chapters...

218
00:15:54,685 --> 00:15:56,725
of his new book,
oh, not two weeks ago.

219
00:15:56,805 --> 00:16:00,405
Plain brown wrapper.
No return address.

220
00:16:02,605 --> 00:16:06,165
Oh, gee, I'm sorry.
You don't mind, do you?

221
00:16:12,205 --> 00:16:14,565
What'd the agent have to say?

222
00:16:14,645 --> 00:16:17,165
You heard what he had to say.

223
00:16:17,245 --> 00:16:19,085
What are you talking about?

224
00:16:19,165 --> 00:16:21,045
I understand you were there...

225
00:16:21,085 --> 00:16:24,285
when the poor man went crazy
in midtown Manhattan.

226
00:16:24,365 --> 00:16:26,645
You witnessed the shooting,
I believe.

227
00:16:26,685 --> 00:16:28,845
That lunatic with the ax?
That was Cane's agent?

228
00:16:30,085 --> 00:16:31,805
Hard to believe, isn't it?

229
00:16:31,885 --> 00:16:35,925
Yeah, well, you'd think a guy
that outsells Stephen King...

230
00:16:36,005 --> 00:16:37,605
couldfind
better representation.

231
00:16:39,685 --> 00:16:41,205
Excuse me.

232
00:16:53,405 --> 00:16:55,165
It's just a little joke.

233
00:16:55,245 --> 00:16:57,365
Well, we're not in the mood.

234
00:16:57,405 --> 00:16:58,805
I'll see you out, Mr. Trent.

235
00:16:58,845 --> 00:16:59,925
Thank you.

236
00:16:59,965 --> 00:17:01,685
Cane is a billion-dollar
franchise.

237
00:17:01,765 --> 00:17:03,285
He's the tent pole
to this company.

238
00:17:03,365 --> 00:17:05,685
We've already sold the film
rights to his new book...

239
00:17:05,725 --> 00:17:08,605
as well as publication rights
in eighteen languages...

240
00:17:08,685 --> 00:17:10,245
The book you can'tfind?

241
00:17:10,325 --> 00:17:12,885
Well, his agentfound it,
at least part of it.

242
00:17:12,965 --> 00:17:15,445
You think he took one look
at this latest work of art...

243
00:17:15,525 --> 00:17:17,685
and went ax-happy
in broad daylight?

244
00:17:17,725 --> 00:17:18,685
I think it's great.

245
00:17:18,765 --> 00:17:21,085
It's great promotion for Arcane,
great publicity.

246
00:17:21,085 --> 00:17:22,965
This was not a publicity stunt.

247
00:17:23,005 --> 00:17:24,125
You were there.

248
00:17:24,205 --> 00:17:26,605
Cane's writing has been known
to have an effect...

249
00:17:26,685 --> 00:17:28,245
on his less stable readers.

250
00:17:28,285 --> 00:17:29,525
An effect? Like what?

251
00:17:29,565 --> 00:17:32,085
Well, disorientation,
memory loss...

252
00:17:32,165 --> 00:17:33,285
severe paranoid reaction.

253
00:17:33,365 --> 00:17:35,805
People pay money
to feel like that? It's cute.

254
00:17:35,885 --> 00:17:37,725
Put it in the press kit.

255
00:17:37,805 --> 00:17:39,965
We need you.

256
00:17:40,045 --> 00:17:43,445
OK. Well, why don't you and I
get together after work?

257
00:17:43,525 --> 00:17:45,245
We'll go through his files.

258
00:17:46,365 --> 00:17:47,605
I don't think so.

259
00:17:47,685 --> 00:17:50,485
I need to see his contracts,
papers, you know.

260
00:17:50,525 --> 00:17:52,765
Impossible.
His agent was a total buffer.

261
00:17:52,845 --> 00:17:55,525
We don't even know
where Cane lives.

262
00:17:55,605 --> 00:17:57,605
What do you know?

263
00:17:57,685 --> 00:17:59,285
For about a year
before he disappeared...

264
00:17:59,325 --> 00:18:02,965
his work became erratic,
