01:07:31,765 --> 01:07:33,405
and nobody pulls my strings.

790
01:07:35,445 --> 01:07:38,765
Did you think my agent
attacked you by accident?

791
01:07:39,925 --> 01:07:42,365
He read about you...
in there.

792
01:07:42,445 --> 01:07:46,205
He knew you'd bring it back
and start the change...

793
01:07:46,285 --> 01:07:48,365
make what's happened here
happen everywhere.

794
01:07:48,405 --> 01:07:50,325
He tried to stop you.

795
01:07:52,085 --> 01:07:54,005
I'm not a piece of fiction.

796
01:07:55,005 --> 01:07:57,165
I think, therefore you are.

797
01:07:59,765 --> 01:08:02,005
Read it if you don't
believe me.

798
01:08:03,285 --> 01:08:05,965
See what I have
in store for you.

799
01:08:07,965 --> 01:08:09,525
I know what I am.

800
01:08:18,645 --> 01:08:19,725
Go back.

801
01:08:21,445 --> 01:08:24,485
Your world lies
beyond that passage.

802
01:08:35,125 --> 01:08:36,925
Go now.

803
01:08:37,005 --> 01:08:40,165
I can't hold them back
any longer.

804
01:09:30,805 --> 01:09:33,365
"Trent stood
at the edge of the rip...

805
01:09:33,405 --> 01:09:37,725
'stared into the illimitable
guif of the unknown...

806
01:09:37,805 --> 01:09:42,365
"the Stygian world
yawning blackly beyond.

807
01:09:42,445 --> 01:09:45,165
'Trent's eyes refused to close.

808
01:09:45,205 --> 01:09:47,125
'He did not shriek...

809
01:09:47,165 --> 01:09:50,485
"but the hideous
unholy abominations...

810
01:09:50,525 --> 01:09:52,485
'shriekedfor him...

811
01:09:52,565 --> 01:09:54,925
'as in the same second
he saw them...

812
01:09:54,965 --> 01:09:57,205
'spill and tumble upward...

813
01:09:57,245 --> 01:10:01,085
'out of an enormous
carrion black pit...

814
01:10:01,165 --> 01:10:04,045
"choked with
the gleaming white bones...

815
01:10:04,125 --> 01:10:07,525
"of countless
unhallowed centuries.

816
01:10:07,565 --> 01:10:09,285
'He began to back away
from the rip...

817
01:10:09,365 --> 01:10:12,085
"as the army
of unspeakable figures...

818
01:10:12,165 --> 01:10:14,805
"twilit by the glow
from the bottomless pit...

819
01:10:14,885 --> 01:10:17,605
'came pouring at him
toward our world."

820
01:10:21,125 --> 01:10:22,285
Come with me.

821
01:10:23,925 --> 01:10:25,445
I can't.

822
01:10:25,525 --> 01:10:28,085
I've read to the end.

823
01:11:41,205 --> 01:11:44,125
Hey, kid.

824
01:11:47,885 --> 01:11:49,325
You want a paper?

825
01:11:56,405 --> 01:11:59,125
Have you been in an accident?

826
01:12:02,205 --> 01:12:04,125
You want me to get somebody?

827
01:12:06,125 --> 01:12:07,525
No. Just...

828
01:12:09,125 --> 01:12:11,725
Just point me to the highway.

829
01:12:11,765 --> 01:12:14,805
Straight up.

830
01:12:19,085 --> 01:12:20,205
Hey, kid.

831
01:12:24,565 --> 01:12:26,805
Did you ever hear of Hobb's End?

832
01:13:57,085 --> 01:13:58,165
What?

833
01:13:58,245 --> 01:14:00,725
Package for you, sir.

834
01:14:00,805 --> 01:14:03,005
But nobody knows I'm here.

835
01:14:03,085 --> 01:14:05,205
Well, someone does.

836
01:14:31,645 --> 01:14:33,165
Who delivered this?

837
01:14:33,205 --> 01:14:34,445
I don't know.

838
01:14:34,485 --> 01:14:35,565
Who?!

839
01:14:35,605 --> 01:14:37,005
I don't know!
I wasn't here last night.

840
01:14:37,045 --> 01:14:38,125
Who was it?!

841
01:14:38,165 --> 01:14:40,685
I was.
And I didn't see shit.

842
01:14:59,445 --> 01:15:03,165
I remember New York
during the Depression.

843
01:15:03,245 --> 01:15:06,285
They think they have it bad now.

844
01:15:06,325 --> 01:15:09,685
You should have seen
the Bowery back then.

845
01:15:09,765 --> 01:15:14,125
Bodies piled two, three feet
high off the gutter.

846
01:15:32,325 --> 01:15:34,205
I'm not going anywhere.

847
01:15:34,285 --> 01:15:37,605
I'm God now.
You understand?

848
01:15:37,685 --> 01:15:40,005
God's not supposed to be
a hack horror writer.

849
01:15:40,085 --> 01:15:43,565
But maybe
I can help you believe.

850
01:15:43,645 --> 01:15:45,365
Look around when you wake up.

851
01:15:45,445 --> 01:15:49,965
Did I ever tell you
my favorite color was blue?

852
01:16:09,765 --> 01:16:11,005
Relax, buddy.

853
01:16:11,085 --> 01:16:13,005
Relax.
You're awake now.

854
01:16:13,085 --> 01:16:16,005
It was just a bad dream.

855
01:16:17,685 --> 01:16:20,045
Are you deaf and dumb, sir?

856
01:16:21,805 --> 01:16:24,645
I was just there in the town...

857
01:16:24,725 --> 01:16:26,645
in that town, and...

858
01:16:26,725 --> 01:16:28,125
there were people there...

859
01:16:28,205 --> 01:16:29,725
and shops and homes and...

860
01:16:29,805 --> 01:16:31,525
I don't doubt that.

861
01:16:31,605 --> 01:16:34,005
What I'm telling you
for the tenth time...

862
01:16:34,085 --> 01:16:36,285
is that it couldn't
have been called Hobb's End.

863
01:16:36,365 --> 01:16:39,685
There never was, is,
or shall be any such place...

864
01:16:39,765 --> 01:16:41,365
by that name in this state.

865
01:16:41,445 --> 01:16:42,565
Ever.

866
01:16:42,645 --> 01:16:44,885
I want to see your supervisor!

867
01:17:28,205 --> 01:17:30,205
Well...

868
01:17:30,285 --> 01:17:32,365
that is quite a story.

869
01:17:32,445 --> 01:17:34,485
If you could write it,
I'd publish it.

870
01:17:36,405 --> 01:17:38,245
You don't believe it, do you?

871
01:17:41,005 --> 01:17:42,565
If I don't, what's my option?

872
01:17:42,645 --> 01:17:45,685
That I'm crazy?

873
01:17:45,805 --> 01:17:47,405
I'm not crazy.

874
01:17:48,405 --> 01:17:50,125
Have you heard the rumors...

875
01:17:50,165 --> 01:17:54,925
that Cane's books
have affected certain readers?

876
01:17:54,965 --> 01:17:57,205
Yeah. Styles told me.

877
01:17:57,285 --> 01:18:01,525
Styles... Oh, that's the girl
you say I sent with you.

878
01:18:01,605 --> 01:18:04,725
But I know I sent you off alone.

879
01:18:04,765 --> 01:18:08,165
Why wouldn't I remember her?

880
01:18:12,725 --> 01:18:14,965
Well...

881
01:18:15,005 --> 01:18:17,765
That's easy.
She was written out.

882
01:18:17,845 --> 01:18:19,365
Written out?

883
01:18:19,445 --> 01:18:22,405
Look, do you think...

884
01:18:22,485 --> 01:18:25,325
those books
somehow infected you?

885
01:18:25,405 --> 01:18:27,445
Listen to me, Harglow.

886
01:18:27,525 --> 01:18:31,005
Everything I've said is true.
It's real.

887
01:18:31,085 --> 01:18:34,005
And that's why I had to destroy
the last manuscript.

888
01:18:34,085 --> 01:18:36,965
But I know that's not true.

889
01:18:38,765 --> 01:18:40,085
What are you talking about?

890
01:18:40,165 --> 01:18:43,045
You delivered that manuscript
to me months ago.

891
01:18:43,125 --> 01:18:46,405
To me personally in this room.

892
01:18:46,445 --> 01:18:47,485
I did?

893
01:18:47,565 --> 01:18:50,605
Yes, you did.
Last spring.

894
01:18:50,645 --> 01:18:53,485
For God's sakes,
we published in July.

895
01:18:53,525 --> 01:18:55,165
The book's been in the stores
for seven weeks.

896
01:18:57,565 --> 01:18:58,645
Have you read it?

897
01:18:58,725 --> 01:19:01,245
No.
I never read Cane's work.

898
01:19:01,325 --> 01:19:02,925
I haven't got
the stomach for it.

899
01:19:02,965 --> 01:19:05,845
Pull it.
Don't distribute it.

900
01:19:05,885 --> 01:19:08,845
Even if everything I've said
is totally Looney Tunes...

901
01:19:08,925 --> 01:19:11,565
I know this book
will drive people crazy.

902
01:19:11,605 --> 01:19:14,605
Well, let's hope so.

903
01:19:14,685 --> 01:19:16,805
The movie comes out next month.

904
01:19:18,085 --> 01:19:20,365
Oh, Christ.

905
01:19:28,525 --> 01:19:30,445
The newest, and presumably
posthumous, work...

906
01:19:30,525 --> 01:19:33,845
of Sutter Cane continues
to sit at number one...

907
01:19:33,885 --> 01:19:35,405
on the best-seller list.

908
01:19:35,445 --> 01:19:37,445
'Ln the Mouth of Madness"
is expected to break...

909
01:19:37,525 --> 01:19:40,085
all previous publishing records.

910
01:19:40,205 --> 01:19:42,685
On the local scene, police
are at a loss to explain...

911
01:19:42,725 --> 01:19:46,085
the outbreak of violent crime
among the city's clergy.

912
01:19:46,165 --> 01:19:48,085
The mayor has called
an emergency meeting...

913
01:19:48,165 --> 01:19:50,325
of law enforcement
and medical agencies...

914
01:19:50,365 --> 01:19:54,205
to discuss an apparent epidemic
of paranoid schizophrenia.

915
01:19:54,285 --> 01:19:56,605
Just an unbelievably
horrible story, Bob.

916
01:19:56,685 --> 01:19:58,045
What began locally...

917
01:19:58,125 --> 01:20:00,365
has now broken out
into a global epidemic.

918
01:20:00,405 --> 01:20:02,845
An epidemic
of monumental proportions...

919
01:20:02,925 --> 01:20:06,685
of senseless, seemingly
unmotivated acts of violence.

920
01:20:08,005 --> 01:20:09,045
Like the book?

921
01:20:09,125 --> 01:20:10,565
I love it.

922
01:20:10,645 --> 01:20:13,405
Good.

923
01:20:13,485 --> 01:20:15,565
Then this shouldn't
come as a surprise.

924
01:20:21,205 --> 01:20:23,445
Jeez!
I don't believe he did that!

925
01:20:31,445 --> 01:20:33,205
It's spreading out there,
isn't it?

926
01:20:35,765 --> 01:20:37,525
Just because you know
the symptoms...

927
01:20:37,645 --> 01:20:39,645
doesn't mean to say
your story's true.

928
01:20:39,685 --> 01:20:42,485
It's Cane's story...

929
01:20:42,565 --> 01:20:44,405
and it'll spread
with each new reader.

930
01:20:44,485 --> 01:20:48,205
That's how it gets its power.

931
01:20:48,245 --> 01:20:52,085
What about the people
who don't read?

932
01:20:54,685 --> 01:20:56,605
There's a movie.

933
01:20:58,045 --> 01:20:59,605
Oh, yes, of course.

934
01:21:06,365 --> 01:21:07,845
I'm gonna leave now...

935
01:21:07,925 --> 01:21:10,885
but I'll be coming back,
I promise.

936
01:21:10,965 --> 01:21:12,845
I want to help you.

937
01:21:12,925 --> 01:21:14,005
There's no hurry.

938
01:21:14,085 --> 01:21:16,965
It's safer in here now.

939
01:21:17,045 --> 01:21:19,885
It'll get worse out there.

940
01:21:19,965 --> 01:21:21,085
Why?

941
01:21:24,325 --> 01:21:26,965
Every species can smell
its own extinction.

942
01:21:27,045 --> 01:21:30,005
The last ones left...

943
01:21:30,085 --> 01:21:32,245
won't have a pretty time of it.

944
01:21:32,325 --> 01:21:37,285
And in ten years, maybe less...

945
01:21:37,365 --> 01:21:40,965
the human race
will just be a bedtime story...

946
01:21:41,005 --> 01:21:42,245
for their children.

947
01:21:42,325 --> 01:21:44,925
A myth. Nothing more.

948
01:22:04,565 --> 01:22:07,245
Did he have anything to say?

949
01:22:08,365 --> 01:22:10,645
No. It was useless.

950
01:22:10,725 --> 01:22:13,365
He thinks he's fiction...

951
01:22:13,405 --> 01:22:16,245
and that Sutter Cane's
causing the epidemic.

952
01:22:18,685 --> 01:22:21,965
Do you read Sutter Cane?

953
01:23:14,125 --> 01:23:15,245
Oh, God!

954
01:24:58,165 --> 01:25:00,085
I'll try and continue...

955
01:25:00,125 --> 01:25:03,085
this emergency broadcast as long
as we can hold out here.

956
01:25:03,165 --> 01:25:06,285
Um, the city is almost
completely deserted now.

957
01:25:06,325 --> 01:25:08,725
There are only a few stragglers
left on the streets.

958
01:25:08,765 --> 01:25:10,885
There are
no emergency services.

959
01:25:10,965 --> 01:25:14,085
The fires continue
to burn out of control.

960
01:25:14,165 --> 01:25:17,805
This incredible epidemic
of random mass killing...

961
01:25:17,845 --> 01:25:20,445
has spread to every country
in the civilized world.

962
01:25:20,525 --> 01:25:23,685
Every hour, more people
are becoming infected...

963
01:25:23,725 --> 01:25:27,285
being driven to senseless
acts of extreme violence.

964
01:25:27,285 --> 01:25:29,725
We have gotten reports,
sketchy at best...

965
01:25:29,805 --> 01:25:33,845
of people mutating, their bodies
swelling and distorting...

966
01:25:33,925 --> 01:25:36,205
changing somehow.

967
01:25:36,245 --> 01:25:39,245
Locally, the mass killings
appear to have moved inland.

968
01:25:39,285 --> 01:25:41,725
All the major cities
on the East Coast are silent.

969
01:25:41,805 --> 01:25:43,125
We lost contact
with Los Angeles...

970
01:25:43,165 --> 01:25:44,885
and the West Coast last night...

971
01:25:44,925 --> 01:25:46,765
so it's impossible
at this time to know...

972
01:25:46,805 --> 01:25:49,085
how many unaffected people
are left.

973
01:25:49,165 --> 01:25:52,125
If for any reason...

974
01:25:52,205 --> 01:25:55,045
you are one of us
who hasn't become infected...

975
01:25:55,125 --> 01:25:56,725
take shelter immediately.

976
01:25:56,805 --> 01:25:58,685
Do not trust any friends
orfamily members.

977
01:25:58,765 --> 01:26:01,645
I repeat... Do not...

978
01:26:10,165 --> 01:26:13,165
I'm sorry about the balls!
It was a lucky shot, that's all!

979
01:26:13,205 --> 01:26:14,645
What?!

980
01:26:14,725 --> 01:26:16,925
I am not insane.

981
01:26:17,005 --> 01:26:20,285
Do you hear me?
I am not insane!

982
01:26:23,325 --> 01:26:26,165
Relax, buddy.
You're awake now.

983
01:26:27,765 --> 01:26:30,405
This is not a Sutter Cane story!
This is not reality!

984
01:26:30,485 --> 01:26:32,045
Not reality! Not reality!

985
01:26:32,125 --> 01:26:34,485
This is reality.

